HEADWORD: Impeccability
<hw>Im*pec`ca*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>impeccabilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being
impeccable; exemption from sin, error, or offense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Infallibility and <qex>impeccability</qex> are two of his
attributes.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impeccable</ent>⟦br⟧
